Coat grill rack with nonstick cooking spray before starting the grill. Cut salmon fillets widthwise into 4-in. pieces; place skin side down on grill. Grill, covered, over medium-hot heat for 12-15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Bone, skin and flake salmon; place in a bowl. Add celery, onion and dill. Combine the dressing ingredients; pour over salad and gently toss to coat. Serve or refrigerate; stir before serving.